The paper deals with the task of synthesizing programs from pseudocode using search-based methods. This falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) as well as programming languages (cs.PL). The use of test cases and compilation errors for credit assignment involves techniques from artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques for processing the pseudocode, which falls under computational linguistics (cs.CL).
